==Demographics==
At the [[2000 United States census|2000 census]], there were 2,043 people, 809 households, and 584 families residing in the borough. The population density was {{convert|2,727.6|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 865 housing units at an average density of {{convert|1,154.8|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}.  The [[Race and ethnicity in the United States Census#2000 census|racial makeup]] of the borough was 97.45% White, 0.39% African American, 0.34% Native American, 1.17% Asian, 0.39% from other races, and 0.24% from two or more races. Hispanic or Latino of any race were 1.52%.<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|access-date=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref>

